<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="205" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,690,716]" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">Discussion</emphasis>
. Based on such characters as the oval peritreme, moderately upraised above the evaporatorium, and the dense, erect dorsal vestiture we herein exclude 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Carvalho" authorityYear="1957" box="[711,816,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cylapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stygius">
<emphasis box="[711,816,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">V. stygius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Poppius" authorityYear="1909" box="[881,1047,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Peltidocylapus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[881,1047,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">Peltidocylapus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and we place it in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1860" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Valdasus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">Valdasus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We consequently restore the original combination. Among the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1860" box="[898,998,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Valdasus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[898,998,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">Valdasus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species with a totally dark pronotum, a dorsal length inferior to 
<quantity box="[422,486,799,825]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="205" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
and a patch on exocorium, 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Carvalho" authorityYear="1957" box="[794,899,799,824]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cylapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stygius">
<emphasis box="[794,899,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">V. stygius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is separated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1883" box="[1104,1217,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Valdasus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erebeus">
<emphasis box="[1104,1217,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="205">V. erebeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the wide yellow ring on the first antennal segment.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
